Free Avatar Libraries with Blendshapes
1. Microsoft Rocketbox (Best Option) ⭐
github.com/microsoft/Microsoft-Rocketbox

115 rigged avatars — diverse in race, gender, age, occupation
MIT License — fully free, commercial use OK
15 visemes + 48 FACS blendshapes already included
Designed for research labs doing exactly what you're doing
Some avatars look like working professionals (construction, service, etc.)

Catch: Models are in 3dsMax/FBX format. You'd need to convert to GLB and verify the blendshapes map to what TalkingHead expects (Oculus visemes specifically).

2. Sketchfab — "Rigged T-Pose Human Male w 50 Face Blendshapes"
sketchfab.com/3d-models/rigged-t-pose-human-male-w-50-face-blendshapes-cc7e459...

Free download, CC Attribution license
50 face blendshapes
Photorealistic scan of an actual person
29,000+ downloads — battle-tested

Catch: It's a scan of a specific guy (Mike Alger). Might not match "Geoff" vibe. Would need to verify blendshape names match TalkingHead's requirements.

3. Mixamo Characters (Adobe)
mixamo.com

Free characters with Mixamo-compatible rigs
Easy to download FBX, convert to GLB
Animations included

Catch: Characters are more stylized/game-y. Facial blendshapes may not be included — Mixamo is primarily about body animation.

My Recommendation
Start with Microsoft Rocketbox.

Clone the repo
Browse Docs/all.pdf — it has pictures of all 115 avatars
Find a middle-aged male that looks trustworthy/professional
Grab the blendshape version (not the bone-rigged version)
Convert FBX → GLB in Blender
Run TalkingHead's Blender script to verify/add any missing Oculus visemes

The Rocketbox library was literally built for VR research on avatar embodiment. The blendshapes were added specifically for lip sync (15 visemes + Oculus Lipsync compatibility). This is as close to plug-and-play as you'll get.

